title = "The last 20 years for the equity investor: Making the best of a difficult hand"
+++

The last 20 years have been hard for the equity investor. Returns across asset
classes have been low. Three significant bear markets have seared our minds:
the 2000 dot-com bust, the 2008 GFC and last month's fastest ever bear market
in stock market history. How can an index investor make the best of a difficult
hand?

Perhaps the answer lies in diversification, rebalancing, dollar cost averaging,
and staying the course. To read more, click
[here (pdf)](https://drive.google.com/open?id=18EmjbKOustHqyKgn-Bhl9x6UDWuKBoaj).
